FBIS3-36829 "drsov028_a_94032" FBIS-SOV-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Two Japanese Fishing Boats Caught Poaching PM0902161594 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 9 Feb 94 p 1 PM0902161594 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Anatoliy Prokofyev report under "News" rubric: "Russian Ship Threatens Japanese Fishermen"] [Text] Russian Federation Border Troops -- On 7 February in the southern Kurils sector a Border Troops patrol boat assisted by helicopters arrested two Japanese schooners in Russian territorial waters. When they were inspected, recently caught sea creatures and wet gear were discovered aboard. The poacher ships' captains signed a document attesting to the violation of Russia's state border and illegal fishing. The offending schooners are currently at roadstead in Tyaginskaya Bay. Commenting on this incident, the Russian Federation Border Troops High Command noted that the situation in the central part of the Sea of Okhotsk is now under the strict control of Russian Border Troops naval forces and aviation.
